[4] Canada (ON)
Date: Fri 23 Aug 2013
Source: The Hamilton Spectator [edited]
http://www.thespec.com/news-story/4048074-confirmed-case-of-red-measles-in-hamilton/


Hamilton Public Health Services is investigating after a confirmed case of red[?] measles in a Hamilton adult. The case is travel-related but may have led to other exposures in the city. Public Health is trying to identify individuals who may have been exposed. Anyone who has visited the following locations may have been exposed to measles unless they have already had 2 doses of a measles vaccine, such as MMR or MMRV, or if they have been infected with measles in the past. The locations are:

- Jackson Square Mall, 2 King St. W on 18 Aug 2013, 9 am-2 pm
- Harvest Moon Restaurant, 80 James St. N on 19 Aug 2013, 4-8 pm
- Crowne Plaza, 150 King St. E, in the elevators and Saffron Mediterranean Restaurant and Bar on 18 Aug 2013

Please call public health services at 905-546-2063 if you were at any of these locations at the specified times. "Red measles is highly contagious to those who are susceptible from the beginning of the illness until 4 days later after the rash 1st appears," said Dr. Ninh Tran, associate medical officer of health for Hamilton. Symptoms start with cough, runny nose, red watery eyes and fever. After about 4 days, a rash begins on the face and moves down the body, and there may be white spots inside the mouth. If you think you may have red measles, call public health and call ahead to your doctor's office so that you can wear a mask when you arrive.

--
