[6] USA (TX)
Date: Mon 19 Aug 2013
Source: KENS 5Bio [edited]
http://www.kens5.com/news/SA-parents-fear-measles-outbreak-could-spread-as-kids-return-to-class-220286131.html


A mother's 5-year-old son just started school at Saint Matthew Catholic School on Monday [19 Aug 2013] as reports of a measles outbreak make headlines in North Texas. "As a parent, we're always concerned about sicknesses and diseases for our children," she said. As of Monday [19 Aug 2013], there have been 15 cases reported across the state, with most of the cases in Tarrant County. The child's mother said she's making sure that doesn't happen to her only son, who had a series of 4 shots before school started.

According to the San Antonio Metro Health District, the city hasn't had a measles case since 2007. Dr. Fred Campbell said he's a little surprised that the city has been so fortunate. He hopes that won't change when students return to school. "I think it's something of a problem as far as educators [are concerned] because of the likelihood of this to spread to other children that may not be immune," Campbell said.

[Byline: Brix Fowler]

